 The recent publication on social media of a lion prowling on the Stoffberg road, had many people up in arms, especially after the incident of 14 lions on the loose in Phalaborwa. A photo was published on the Facebook profile of Witbank Parts showing a lion walking next to the road. The administrator of the profile captioned the photo stating that the lion was seen next to the Stoffberg road. It has been confirmed that the sighting was untrue. www.mobserver.co.za tried to reach the owner of the Facebook account for comment but they did not respond before publication of the article. The image has since been deleted from the account.     More fatalities after bus accident on Stoffberg road Municipality makes gruesome discovery in blocked drain Horrific accident: Ten casualties airlifted to Mpumalanga hospitals VIDEO – Peeing in public, a nuisance of note • Save our standby number (072 248 3855) and send us a WhatsApp message with the words “Add me” to be added to our broadcast list. • Like us on Facebook, follow us on Twitter and Instagram. • Subscribe to our YouTube channel. • Click on the link to subscribe to our bi-weekly newsletter via email. Contact our news room on our 24 hr standby number 072 248 3855, or send a mail to our editor tobie@mobserver.co.za